related_questions.question: What are long-term tax-exempt bonds?
related_questions.snippet: Municipal bonds are generally referred to as tax-exempt bonds because the interest earned on the bonds often is excluded from gross income for federal income tax purposes and, in some cases, is also exempt from state and local income taxes.

list: Vanguard Tax-Exempt Bond ETF (VTEB): This is an exchange-traded fund (ETF) that invests in a broad portfolio of investment-grade municipal bonds.
Vanguard Short-Term Tax-Exempt Bond ETF (VTES): Another ETF, this one focuses on short-term municipal bonds.
Vanguard California Tax-Exempt Bond ETF (VTEC): A state-specific ETF for California investors seeking tax-exempt income.
Vanguard Long-Term Tax-Exempt Bond ETF (VTEL): A recently launched ETF providing long-term tax-exempt bond exposure.
Vanguard New York Tax-Exempt Bond ETF (MUNY): A recently launched ETF providing New York-specific tax-exempt bond exposure.
Vanguard Limited-Term Tax-Exempt Fund (VMLTX): A mutual fund that invests in short-term, high-quality municipal bonds.
Vanguard High-Yield Tax-Exempt Fund (VWATX): A mutual fund focused on high-yield municipal bonds.
Vanguard Tax-Exempt Bond Index Fund (VTEAX): A mutual fund that tracks a specific municipal bond index.
Vanguard Municipal Money Market Fund (VMSXX): A money market fund that invests in short-term municipal securities.
Vanguard Core Tax-Exempt Bond ETF (VCRM): An actively managed ETF focused on core tax-exempt bonds.
Vanguard Short Duration Tax-Exempt Bond ETF (VSDM): An actively managed ETF focused on short duration tax-exempt bonds.
Vanguard Long-Term Tax-Exempt Fund (VWLTX): A mutual fund focused on long-term municipal bonds.
